---
title: Version Control for Business
layout: post
comments: true
---

As a programmer, we use git. I knew that coming to Deloitte would be a shock in many ways. The biggest thing though is version control. As a programmer, we have a lot of tools at our disposal to do good version control. It’s a surprise to me that most of the business world is still mired in archaic systems of synchronization. If I want to update a powerpoint desk, I usually have to send the whole powerpoint to my coworker. Now this isn’t usually a big deal, because it’s just two of us right now and the powerpoints are small. But imagine a *team* of people separately working on a huge powerpoint. That’s a nightmare. The same problem, of course, exists when editing word documents or excel files. 

